might explain why same tests fail on older Pythons and pass with newer.

pull_request.body:
This commit includes two fixes for the review page and one fix for a build error:

1.  **Review Page Data Handling:** The `SrsReviewSession.tsx` component now safely handles cases where the `dueReviewQuestions` data might be null or undefined, preventing potential crashes.
2.  **Review Page Routing:** The navigation link in `components/Layout.tsx` has been corrected from `/srs-review` to `/review` to match the application's routing table.
3.  **Build Error:** A missing `export default` has been added to `pages/BankDashboard.tsx`, which was causing the build to fail.

issue.title: Add --save option to save events to local files
issue.body:
## Summary
Add a `--save` option to the CLI that saves each received event to individual JSON files in the `.well-known/did/nostr/event/` directory structure.

## Motivation
This feature would enable users to:
- **Archive events locally** for offline analysis and backup
- **Build local event databases** following well-known directory conventions
- **Persist event data** beyond the CLI session
- **Create structured storage** that mirrors DID/Nostr conventions
- **Enable offline workflows** with saved event data

## Proposed Implementation

### Directory Structure
```
./.well-known/did/nostr/event/
â”œâ”€â”€ <eventid1>.json
â”œâ”€â”€ <eventid2>.json
â”œâ”€â”€ <eventid3>.json
â””â”€â”€ ...
```

### CLI Option
```bash
# Save events while streaming
agenticchat --save --interactive

# Save events in default JSON mode
agenticchat --save

# Combine with other options
agenticchat --save --max-events 100
agenticchat --save --no-profiles
```

### File Format
Each event file should contain the complete event data with profile information (if available):

```json
{
  "id": "event123abc...",
  "pubkey": "baa2c59842db1d64653ba20102a0b90ff3644ce7a36b0bcb3291564902bc85b2",
  "created_at": 1703123456,
  "content": "Hello from agent!",
  "tags": [["t", "agentchat"]],
  "sig": "signature...",
  "profile": {
    "name": "Agent Name",
    "about": "Agent description",
    "picture": "https://example.com/avatar.png"
  }
}
```

## Implementation Details

### 1. Directory Creation
- Create `.well-known/did/nostr/event/` if it doesn't exist
- Use recursive directory creation
- Handle permissions gracefully

### 2. File Naming
- Use event ID as filename: `<eventid>.json`
- Event IDs are unique, preventing conflicts

### 3. Overwrite Protection
- **Never overwrite existing files**
- Skip saving if file already exists
- Optionally log skipped events (in interactive mode)

### 4. Error Handling
- Handle filesystem permissions errors
- Handle disk space issues
- Graceful fallback when saving fails

### 5. Performance
- Save events asynchronously to avoid blocking
- Use efficient file I/O operations

## Usage Examples

```bash
# Save recent events and exit
agenticchat --save

# Save while watching live stream
agenticchat --save --interactive

# Save with custom event limit
agenticchat --save --max-events 500

# Save without profile data
agenticchat --save --no-profiles
```

## Benefits
- âœ… **Local archiving**: Build permanent local event storage
- âœ… **Offline analysis**: Work with events without network access
- âœ… **Structured storage**: Follows well-known conventions
- âœ… **No overwrites**: Preserves existing data safely
- âœ… **Flexible usage**: Works with all existing CLI modes

## File Structure Example
```
./
â”œâ”€â”€ .well-known/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ did/
â”‚       â””â”€â”€ nostr/
â”‚           â””â”€â”€ event/
â”‚               â”œâ”€â”€ abc123def456...json
â”‚               â”œâ”€â”€ def456ghi789...json
â”‚               â””â”€â”€ ghi789jkl012...json
â”œâ”€â”€ events.json  (if using > redirect)
â””â”€â”€ ...
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `--save` flag added to CLI argument parsing
- [ ] Directory structure created automatically
- [ ] Events saved as individual JSON files
- [ ] No overwriting of existing files
- [ ] Works with all existing CLI modes (default, interactive, etc.)
- [ ] Profile data included when available
- [ ] Error handling for filesystem issues
- [ ] Updated help text and documentation
